<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181804" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mantilla Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mantilla">Pheidole mantilla</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Types LNBio.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181804" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mantilla Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mantilla Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mantilla">mantilla</taxonomicName>
, cloak, referring to the dense pilosity of the head and mesosoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">
diagnosis Closely similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33650" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole caribbaea Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole caribbaea Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbaea">caribbaea</taxonomicName>
of Jamaica, differing in the major in its narrower occiput seen in full-face view; carinulae of the cephalic dorsum reaching all the way to the occiput border; shorter scape; oval (rather than trapezoidal) postpetiole; and lighter (reddish-yellow as opposed to brown) color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.32, HL 1,42, SL 1.02, EL 0.20, PW 0.62.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.80, SL 1.04, EL 0.16, PW 0.40.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Color Major: concolorous medium reddish yellow (&quot;orange&quot;).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Minor: concolorous brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">Range Northern Pacific lowlands of Costa Rica.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="323">biology Longino (1997) found the species in open habitats of seasonally dry areas. Workers forage on the ground and up into low vegetation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
